items.title:
org.opentmf.client:opentmf-v4-clients 1.1.4 发布, TMF Clients is a TMF-630 compliant generic client implementation which uses Spring Webflux
    to communicate with a TMF compliant backend.

    The following features are provided out of the box:
    - Uses the dynamically decomposable opentmf-v4-models library for the hierarchical TMF model classes.
    - Supports dnext-opentmf-v4-models and similar model extensions.
    - Ability to use any configured opentmf-web-clients for dynamic access token retrieval
    - Ability to specify only the requested columns
    - Ability to apply a jsonPath at server-side or client-side
    - Ability to retrieve a payload as the desired object type
    - Ability to retrieve one page, all pages at once, or any desired page at a time
    - Provides methods with and without access token parameters
    - Follows TMF-630 recommendations.

items.title:
edu.hm.hafner:codingstyle-pom 5.30.0 发布, Each Java project should follow a given coding style. I.e., all contributions to the source code should use the same
    formatting rules, design principles, code patterns, idioms, etc. I published such a coding style in my
    GitHub project codingstyle (https://github.com/uhafner/codingstyle) - I am using this coding style in my lectures
    about software development at Munich University of Applied Sciences and in all of my open source projects.

    If you want to use this coding style as well, you can use this Maven POM as parent of your own POM. Then you
    get the configuration several static analysis and testing tools for free.

items.title:
org.opentmf.client:opentmf-clients-base 1.1.4 发布, OpenTMF Clients Base is a TMF-630 compliant generic client implementation which uses Spring's
		reactive WebClient to communicate with a TMF compliant backend.

		The following features are provided out of the box:
		- Uses the dynamically decomposable tmf-models library for the hierarchical TMF model classes.
		- Supports dnext-tmf-models and sh-tmf-models extensions.
		- Ability to use any configured pia-web-clients for dynamic access token retrieval
		- Ability to specify only the requested columns
		- Ability to apply a jsonPath at server-side or client-side
		- Ability to retrieve a payload as the desired object type
		- Ability to retrieve one page, all pages at once, or any desired page at a time
		- Provides methods with and without access token parameters
		- Follows TMF-630 recommendations.
